CRIMEAN-CONGO HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever - South Africa 980317225152
Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever - South Africa (02) 980318224213
Date: Mon, 02 Nov 1998 10:28:51 +0200
Source: Weekly Mail and Guardian, Johannesburg, RSA
Via: David Basckin <kingbee@iafrica.com>

On Friday a 25-year-old farmer from North-West province was admitted to
Johannesburg's Garden City Clinic with Congo fever [Crimean-Congo
hemorrhagic fever = C-CHF, caused by C-CHF virus, a virus of the genus
_Nairovirus_ of the family Bunyaviridae. - Mod.CHC. The patient had high
fever and internal bleeding on admission to the clinic. Congo fever is
endemic to South Africa and treatment is routine. The disease is contracted
from the bite of the bont-legged tick, found in dry Northern Cape regions.
The patient is believed to have contracted the disease while on holiday at
a game farm near Vaalwater in the Northern Province. His condition is
stable but he remains in isolation.
--
David Basckin, independent journalist
Box 50338, Musgrave 4062
South Africa
TEL: 083-3072132
