e-mail: kingbee@iafrica.com
[This article said that Congo fever is "one of the viral haemorrhagic
fevers related to Ebola" but "is not as severe as Ebola fever". In fact,
these two diseases are related only insofar as they are hemorrhagic fevers.
C-CHF is caused by a member of the family Bunyaviridae (ibid), Ebola fever
is caused by a member of the family Filoviridae. C-CHF is treated with
ribavirin.
Our own Jack Woodall was the author of one of the first articles regarding
isolation of Congo virus, from the blood of a human in Zaire. It was later
shown that Crimean hemorrhagic fever was cause by the same virus, hence the
portmanteau phrase "C-CHF virus". - Mod.CHC
